94
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:05,600
Near the tail end of World War II in 1945,

95
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:07,700
at what was called the Yalta Conference,

96
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:11,830
the US wanted the Soviet Union to join the
war against the Japanese.

97
00:04:11,830 --> 00:04:12,960
One of the conditions was

98
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:17,280
that the area we now know as Outer Mongolia
would be independent.

99
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:20,979
Well, not so much independent as a Soviet
satellite state.

100
00:04:20,979 --> 00:04:23,000
Now remember, at the time,

101
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,669
China was ruled by the Republic of China government,

102
00:04:25,669 --> 00:04:27,900
which was also a US ally.

103
00:04:27,900 --> 00:04:31,169
And since they were too weak at the time to
challenge the Soviets,

104
00:04:31,169 --> 00:04:34,300
they agreed to it if the Soviet Union agreed
not to support

105
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:36,120
the Communists inside China.

106
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:39,499
A few years later, the Communists took over
China anyway,

107
00:04:39,499 --> 00:04:41,960
and formed the People’s Republic of China.

108
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:44,000
They weren’t able to challenge the Soviets
either.

109
